==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spank
<hw>Spank</hw> <pr>(sp⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Spanked</conjf>
<pr>(sp⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧kt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Spanking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Of unknown origin; cf. LG.
<ets>spakken</ets>, <ets>spenkern</ets>, to run and spring about
quickly.]</ety> <def>To strike, as the breech, with the open hand; to
slap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spank</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spank
<hw>Spank</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A blow with the open hand; a
slap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spank</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Spank
<hw>Spank</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To move with a quick, lively step
between a trot and gallop; to move quickly.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spanker</ent>⟦br⟧
